sources.title: T-Bird Gang
sources.description: After Frank's father, a night watchman, was murdered in the robbery of the warehouse that he was guarding, with the police knowing that it was the Hendricks mob who committed the murder but not having any evidence to arrest or convict them. Frank (John Brinkley) going all over town trying to find and join the Hendricks mob runs into to it and it's leader Alex Hendricks (Edwin Nelson).

sources.title: T-Bird Gang (1959) ROGER CORMAN
sources.description:
Movie Class by PizzaFLIX: Legendary cult filmmaker Roger Corman has directed
over 50 films and produced nearly 400 more. In the process he helped launch the careers
of Jack Nicholson, Robert De Niro, Charles Bronson, Sylvester Stallone, Francis Ford Coppola, Martin Scorsese, Ron Howard, Robert Towne, Peter Bogdanovich, and James Cameron!

Stars: John Brinkley, Ed Nelson, Tony Miller
Director: Richard Harbinger
Producer: Roger Corman/Sparta Productions

Seeking to revenge the murder of his father, a high school student goes undercover and joins a deadly gang of juvenile delinquents.

sources.title: T-Bird Gang (1959) Drama, Thriller Full Length Movie
sources.description:
The one year out of high school crowd--fast cars, girls . . . no place to go! 
A high school boy, out to find his father's killer, joins up with a gang of juvenile delinquents.
 
Director: Richard Harbinger
Writers: John Brinkley, Tony Miller
Producer: Roger Corman
Stars: John Brinkley, Ed Nelson, Tony Miller
Genres: Drama, Thriller
